<br>
It's one thing to be proud of where your roots come from. It's another to demand special rights because of them. I've had black people come up to me, screaming, that *I* oppressed their people and threw them into slavery. Nope, sorry... I'm not old enough to have...and if you want to go back to my family's heritage... I'm Irish. My family were a bunch of horse thieves and Pagans. We didn't come over until the early 1900's or so. <br>
<br>
Before you point a finger and say that the white people oppressed yours, you might want to do some studying on that. Slavery was around long before the &quot;White Man&quot; came onto African soil. Africans were enslaving Africans. Romans, Native Americans, Greeks, you name it. I don't think there was one society that DIDN'T have slavery in their heritage.<br>
<br>
You want to have pride in your roots, I don't have a problem with that. Hell, I'd even celebrate them with you. But don't hide behind them because you think you deserve special treatment because that's a bunch of bull. <br>
<br>
I applaud Iskur's speech. He doesn't make this a race issue and so long as people continue seeing it AS a race issue, we WILL have racists all over the world. There is only ONE race here...and it's the HUMAN race. The moment you take off your color filtered glasses and see this, the happier we will ALL be. <p><!--EZCODE FONT START--><span style="color:purple;"><!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>Mysidia Drakkenbane</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--></span><!--EZCODE FONT END-->: 51 Human Druid<br>
