<br>
To me, there's a distinct difference between being a racist and being a bigot (prejudice).  I think almost all black people are racist, but I also think a lot of black people are prejudice.  The difference is this.  I think a racist takes pride in his own race without putting down others.  Example, I think every black person is proud that there are a few black people in hockey and if that person succeeds, it's seen as someone who &quot;made it.&quot;  The same goes for Tiger Woods and so on.  It's viewed as a pioneered moment.  Same thing goes for the Black Expression ordeal.  I just see it as a chance for people to see a side that many don't know about it.  A side away from all the Jay-Z's and the 50 Cent's and the Al Sharptons.  To salute the movement is one thing.  To denounce the movement or another or more importantly, place blame on other races for their own faults is another.<br>
<br>
Hell, I know very few knew that I was black and it shouldn't matter.  But there are just reactions that people have upon that.  Like I remember the first time I told someone that on tells in EQ.  They said, &quot;Black people play Everquest?&quot;  Or just a few moments ago at work.  I have an accent and although I use slang often, I speak and type properly. One of my co-workers said that I was &quot;talking white.&quot;  I shrugged her off, but that's the stuff that I go through every day.  I can not stress how proud my peers are of my accomplishments in school.  They say, &quot;we need more people like you to undo the stereotypical image caused by black people and unfortunately the image embedded into the mindframe of some white people.&quot;<br>
<br>
I thought that was a joke until I saw some of the posts in this thread.<br>
<br>
No white person has enslaved me.  I know this.  I know that we enslaved ourselves (although from what I've read, slavery in Africa was not as severe as what was done in the states).  It's a crutch used to justify laziness.  Welfare and Affirmative Action are also justifications of laziness.  I don't believe in Ebonics.  Learn the proper language.  I speak four languages fluently.  I know others that do too.  But on that same note, don't let what you see out there from radicals and dumbfucks ruin the perpetual image of what really goes on.<br>
<br>
There are many whom are diligently trying to correct it. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#deddbf><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub228.ezboard.com/bxevserverboards.showUserPublicProfile?gid=mysidiadrakkenbane>MysidiaDrakkenbane</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://image1ex.villagephotos.com/extern/724222.jpg" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Bitch with the Ban Stick</span><br>  Posts: 2324<br> <font color=#330000>(10/10/03 1:47 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub228.ezboard.com/fxevserverboardsfrm6.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1060.topic&index=85>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> <BR><img src=http://image1ex.villagephotos.com/1829785.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Mother fucking racist horsehit pisses me off</span><hr size=1> /cheer Ishkur<br>
